function loadBook(toData)
    base.books.AddLanguage("dwarf language",toData);
    
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "Within this book you will find the written speech of our great King, founding father of Silverbrand, on behalf of our town.", 0, 0,toData);
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "Dear citizens, allies and friends of Silverbrand,", 0, 0,toData);
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "Silverbrand was no gift from the gods, it's the result of hard work of the founder dwarves, who digged the first caverns with their own hands, who payed every brick, every anvil and every furnace", 0, 0,toData);
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "with their gold. This town was build using a total of more than 10.000 silvercoins (translated to current prices) which was payed by the founder dwarves alone.", 0, 0,toData); 
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "3/4 of this sum 10 dwarves payed and worked for all on their own, I myself have contributed about 5000 coins.", 0, 0,toData);
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "Rugosch, Bombor, Caranthir and Gandela contributed about 1000 silvercoins, each through his own hard work.", 0, 0,toData);
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "All founder dwarves agreed that every dwarf may find a home in this town if he is willing to proclaim the oath of trust.", 0, 0,toData); 
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "These dwarves, which buildings you take as if they'd been gifted by someone and which you use as if it'd be natural have decided that I should be king.", 0, 0,toData);
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "Bombor smithed my crown with his own hands, Rugosch as the highest priest of Irmorom in this lands crowned me during a big festivity. ", 0, 0,toData);
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "All dwarves that helped to build the town spoke their oath on myself, and thus elected myself to be the guardian of the finances, the lord and overseer over their work (the town) for my lifetime. ", 0, 0,toData); 
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "Even Irmoroms voice could be heard on the day of the coronation, blessing our kingdom and our work. ", 0, 0,toData);
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "I demand respect from all who use the gifts these fouder dwarves have brought to us and live in Silverbrand. Only the elves have done simmilar to the dwarves, creating a similar kingdom on their ", 0, 0,toData);
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "island. Nevertheless us dwarves were the first to have an own kingdom and that is one thing that shall never be forgotten. ", 0, 0,toData); 
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "And to stop the forgetting hear my voice and read my words. ", 0, 0,toData);
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "Never forget that it were 3 dwarves who sat at a campfire and decided: WE WILL BUILD A TOWN, FOR US DWARVES ONLY. These three whose idea incited a burning desire in ", 0, 0,toData);
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "the hearts of the dwarves were Bombor, Rugosch and Tialdin, and immediately, others followed: Caranthir, Gandela, Torekin, Galim, Belegi, Josef, Ingrain, Grimbart, Whisler, Rackere, Mishrak,", 0, 0,toData); 
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "Crotkin and many others but the ones listed where those who gave the most to help build this town.", 0, 0,toData);
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "Now I hear the question why there's an oath and why Silverbrand is a monarchy with a soveign wielding absolute power.", 0, 0,toData);
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "I answer this question: The founder dwarves wanted it to be like that. Every dwarf that comes to Silverbrand is a guest of those first dwarves, who have elected me to be their ", 0, 0,toData); 
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "king. Every dwarf that proclaims his oath, so these dwarves have decided, may call Silverbrand his home. ", 0, 0,toData);
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "The only demand they ask is respect for their work. Respect and obedience for the king. ", 0, 0,toData);
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "Who doesn't want to respect the founder dwarves should decide to find a new home, before he takes the oath. ", 0, 0,toData); 
    base.books.AddEnglishBookText( "Tialdin, King of Silverbrand ", 0, 0,toData);
    
